-- Airlines in China Cut Commissions for Domestic Tickets, Newspaper Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-06T23:53:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/airlines-in-china-cut-commissions-for-domestic-tickets-newspaper-reports.html

          
          
             Air China Ltd., China Southern
Airlines Co. and China Eastern Airlines Corp. have reduced the
commissions they pay to agents for selling tickets aboard
domestic flights, China Business News reported July 5, citing
unidentified ticketing agents.  
 China Eastern and its unit Shanghai Airlines cut
commissions for flights departing Beijing to 3 percent from July
3, the Shanghai-based newspaper reported, without saying what
the rate was cut from.  
 Air China cut commissions on flights leaving Shanghai by
about 2 percentage points to 3 percent, according to the report,
which didnâ€™t say when the cut took place. China Southern reduced
its commission on tickets for all flights departing Shanghai by
about 2 percentage points, according to the report, without
saying what the rate was cut to or when the cut was implemented.  
 China Southern was the first to reduce commissions on
international flights, the Shanghai-based newspaper reported on
its website.  
